title: High Five construction 2003

pageHeader.title: Construction of the High Five Interchange

text: These photos are from October and December 2003. The High Five Interchange was completed in November 2005.

Looking north along US 75 (Central Expressway)
Looking northwest with the frontage road in the foreground and the eastbound IH-635 main lanes in the midground.

Looking east from the Coit overcrossing on the west side of the interchange. The originally planned paint scheme was much lighter in color, as shown in this photo. The paint colors were changed to darker colors for the final paint. (photo by Jeremy Murphy)
A wider view looking west along IH 635 from the Coit Road overpass. (photo by Jeremy Murphy)
The new eastbound frontage road under construction at IH 635. (photo by Jeremy Murphy)
Looking east along IH 635. Ramp construction is nearing completion and the segmental assembly machine will soon be retired from service. (photo by Jeremy Murphy)
Looking southeast at the connection ramps (photo by Jeremy Murphy)
Looking south-southeast

This view looks south along Central Expressway (US 75) on the north side of the interchange. Visible in the distance is the newly opened ramp from I-635 eastbound to US 75 northbound. (photo by Jeremy Murphy)
This is the ramp exiting from US 75 southbound, for connections to IH 635. (photo by Jeremy Murphy)
Looking west on the east side of the interchange.
Looking east on the east side of the interchange, from the same overcrossing as the above photo. This view shows the long length of the connection ramps. (photo by Jeremy Murphy)
Looking east on the east side of the interchange (photo by Jeremy Murphy)

Column painting in progress at the Greenville/DART rail overpass. These colors have the original light colors, and the right column appears to have the darker final color near the ground. (photo by Jeremy Murphy)
TI (Texas Instruments) Boulevard exit on IH 635 (photo by Jeremy Murphy)
